					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't know but I'd double check the initialisation of IRQs at reset. At reset you'd probably want to set the interrupt flag (at least until you actually expect IRQs), write #$00 to $4015 to disable all channels (especially DMC), and read $4015 after that (so it would acknownledge any possible interrupt to be safe).
<br />I know the NES is supposed to disable all sound channels and IRQs when it's soft-resetted, but just to be sure...</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
